javaEventing
Class MultiEventWatcher

java.lang.Object
  javaEventing.MultiEventWatcher

public class MultiEventWatcher
extends java.lang.Object

Helper-class for subscribing to multiple events. Use this class when actions should be taken if event x OR event y is triggered. Copyright 2011 Espen Skjervold, FFI

Method Detail

addEvent

public void addEvent(EventManager.Event event)
Registers an event for the multi-event watcher to watch. Any number of events can be registered.

Parameters:
event - The events the multi-event watcher will subsribe to.

addEvent

public void addEvent(EventManager.Event event,
                     EventManager.Condition condition)
Registers an event for the multi-event watcher to watch. Any number of events can be registered.

Parameters:
event - The events the multi-event watcher will subsribe to.
condition - Each registered event may have a specific condition in order for the watcher to be notified. One may mix and match with events with and without condtions.

waitForAnyEvent

public boolean waitForAnyEvent(long timeout)
Blocking call. The thread execution will freeze until one of the registered events are triggered.

Parameters:
timeout - The number of milliseconds before unblocking the call, regardless of whether or not any of the events are triggered. If zero, it will never time out.

waitForAllEvents

public boolean waitForAllEvents(long timeout)
Blocking call. The thread execution will freeze until all of the registered events are triggered.

Parameters:
timeout - The number of milliseconds before unblocking the call, regardless of whether or not all the events have been triggered. If zero, it will never time out.

waitForAllEventsThenUnregister

public boolean waitForAllEventsThenUnregister(long timeout)
Blocking call. The thread execution will freeze until all of the registered events are triggered. After notified, the watcher will automatically unregister internal listeners.

Parameters:
timeout - The number of milliseconds before unblocking the call, regardless of whether or not all the events have been triggered. If zero, it will never time out.

waitForAnyEventThenUnregister

public boolean waitForAnyEventThenUnregister(long timeout)
Blocking call. The thread execution will freeze until one of the registered events are triggered. After notified, the watcher will automatically unregister its internal listener.

Parameters:
timeout - The number of milliseconds before unblocking the call, regardless of whether or not any of the events are triggered. If zero, it will never time out.
